Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` must not be null.
- The length of the input array `nums` must be greater than or equal to 1.
- The length of the input array `nums` must be less than or equal to 40.
- Each element in the input array `nums` must be an integer.
- Each element in the input array `nums` must be greater than or equal to -10^7.
- Each element in the input array `nums` must be less than or equal to 10^7.
- The input integer `goal` must be greater than or equal to -10^9.
- The input integer `goal` must be less than or equal to 10^9.

Postconditions:
- The output integer must be the minimum possible value of `abs(sum - goal)`, where `sum` is the sum of the elements in the chosen subsequence of `nums`.
- The output integer must be greater than or equal to 0.